  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: 1-1 chat contains active request message (with blinking icon). After user sends ether using send command this requesting message becomes inactive (icon is not blinking), so tap on request message does not add \"/send recipient amount\" to the input field. Expected: if request message was not used it should be active.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n if request message was not used it should be active.\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAfter user sends ether using send command this requesting message becomes inactive (icon is not blinking), so tap on request message does not add \"/send recipient amount\" to the input field.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7R20tdFlLZVhfQ0k\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1-1 chat with active request message received from another user\r\n- send to this user some ether (do not use request message, just use send command)\r\n- after ether is sent: check that you can tap on requesting message in 1-1 chat and it's active \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop 0.9.8-68-g458c8844+\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S7, Android 7.0\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.2.1",
